(non-refundable)  $175    Full-time Tuition - Full Semester  $5,500    Part-time Tuition - Full Semester  $3,300    Midterm Entry Tuition  $3,300    Part-time Midterm Entry Tuition  $1,980          Health Insurance   As a part of this ESL program costs, all students are required by the University of Illinois to have health insurance. Some students have health insurance through their scholarship or program. Our ESL program offers a health insurance policy for F-1 students. The cost of international student health insurance through the Tutorium is below.  Students with other health insurance and students who are not F-1 do not pay for health insurance at the office. However , you must show proof of health insurance valid in the United States. Your proof of insurance must include these minimum requirements:   Name of student  Dates of coverage  Sickness Minimum coverage of $50,000 USD per incident  Injury Minimum coverage of $50,000 USD per incident  In English  U.S. contact information listed   F-1 students (not citizens or residents) must also include:   Repatriation ($7,800 USD minimum)  Expenses associated with medical evacuation ($10,000 USD minimum)       Tutorium International Student Health Insurance Fees         Full Session  Midterm Entry    Spring  $478  $292    Summer  $375  $215    Fall  $550  $350          Disclaimers    If you have any dependents, we strongly recommend you get health insurance for them before you arrive in Chicago.  No institutional scholarships or financial aid for tuition is available.  Program costs are subject to change.        Intensive English Program Refund Policy   If you cannot attend the session you originally applied for, notify the Tutorium .  The nonrefundable application fee can be used for the next I-20 and session only.  For future sessions, a new application fee and other documents will be required for registration.  A full refund of fees, excluding the application fee and service charges, is issued if the Tutorium receives notification before the Placement Exam .  A partial refund is issued through the second week of class.  No refunds are made after the second week of class.      Full Session Refund Schedule    100% refund (minus $20 service fee for credit card payments) with notification by the Friday before the Placement Exam  95% by the Friday before classes begin  85% through the first week of classes  65% through the second week of classes     No refunds are made after the second week of classes. The $175 application fee is non-refundable.     Midterm Entry Refund Schedule    100% refund (minus $20 service fee for credit card payments) with notification by the Friday before the Placement Exam  85% through the first week of classes     No refunds are made after the first week of classes.  The $175 application fee is non-refundable.          Pay Intensive English Program Fees          Intensive English    Back to main content           IEP Courses    IEP Tuition & Fees    I-20 & Visa    Tutorium Start Dates    Transfer Students    Current Students     COVID-19 Information and FAQs    Intensive English Program Student Handbook    IEP Textbook List    Tech Requirements for Online Study    Cool Websites for ESL Students      Pay fees                      UIC Logo        The Tutorium         Main Menu    Intensive English    Other Programs    Student Life    About Us    How to Apply      IEP    IEP Courses    IEP Tuition & Fees    IEP Start Dates    Pay Fees    Current Students      More Info    I-20 & Visa    English for International Professionals    Contact Us        Quick Links    Request Information    Apply    Pay Fees         Contact   Tutorium in Intensive English  1333 South Halsted Street, Suite 260 Chicago, Illinois 60607-5019 USA  Phone: +1-312-996-8098  Fax: +1-312-996-4394  tutorium@uic.edu        Social Media Accounts    Facebook    Instagram             UIC.edu links   UIC.edu  Academic Calendar  Athletics  Campus Directory  Disability Resources  Emergency Informat